description:
The Green Hornet is back and Dynamite is the new home for the avenging hero and his faithful sidekick, Kato (and, the Black Beauty, 'natch!)!

And we're kicking things off with a BANG as we launch the first of a new series of adventures starting with the great Kevin Smith. And let's get it out of the way, right here, right NOW - the scripts are in! Every single one! Joining Smith in bringing his unproduced screenplay to life is artist Jonathan (Black Terror) Lau as they present the one and only origin of the Green Hornet and Kato. This is the comic book version of Kevin Smith's unproduced Green Hornet film and Dynamite is the only place to get in on the action - it all begins here!

name: Episode One: Night And Day

description: As Jepperd hits rock bottom, memories of his chilling past resurface. And Gus finally comes face-to-face with the ominous Dr. Singh, a man at the center of the post-apocalyptic mystery.
name: In Captivity, Part 2

description: Veronica meets President Obama in this very special issue! When the teens go to Washington on a class trip, they visit all the historic sites, including the Washington Monument, Lincoln Memorial, and more! They also have an opportunity to meet President Obama in a question and answer session. Taking the President's message about job creation to heart, Veronica puts Archie to work at Lodge Mansion - conveniently forgetting to tell her dad! She also gives Betty a job, strictly to keep her away from Archie! Will Veronica help stimulate the economy, or will she merely help stimulate her father's anger?
name: Ms. Lodge Goes to Washington, Part 1

description: In the conclusion of SPAWN: ENDGAME, reporter Marc Rosen connects the miracle patient stories to the new SPAWN, Jim Downing, as detectives Sam, Twitch and Rowand discover the association between Downing's awakening, Bill Winston's suicide and the Nortego crime syndicate.
name: Endgame Conclusion

description: So where are the good superheroes? The warriors for truth and justice, the defenders of the American way? The supes can't all be dirtbags... can they? Meet the true heroes of The Boys' universe, the young men and women who fight to make things right and ask nothing in return: the teenage adventurers from our far future that the world knows as SUPERDUPER! Meanwhile, convinced that Hughie was never what he seemed, Butcher goes to see the Legend- and sets something terrible in motion for our little Scots pal...
name: The Innocents, Part One

description: Tom√°s Giorello returns to full penciling duties-with the remarkable colors of Jos√© Villarrubia fleshing out each page-and Timothy Truman scripts this first episode in a new, three-issue story arc entitled "Kozaki"! After burning a few bridges and making some questionable choices, mainly fueled by jealousy over Prince Julion's recent appearance in Khoraja and a hatred for pampered royalty and their courtly life, Conan leaves Yasmela and her palace behind. Now leading Amalric's mercenary army, Conan is again responsible for the lives of others. But is he skilled and experienced enough to do the job right? In this issue, we'll also discover more bleak premonitions and clues concerning Conan's near future, when Conan and his companions leave organized mercenary life behind in order to survive as a group of raiders and looters. Such actions will undoubtedly draw the attentions of others, though, and the troubles that began for Conan in the previous "Free Companions" arc are far from over!
name: Kozaki (Part 1)

description: Rick Deckard is under arrest! Thanks to the notorious Nexus-6 android Luba Luft, Deckard finds himself in his biggest predicament yet. Is Deckard a human - or an android? Everything is not as it seems in this exciting issue of the Philip K. Dick masterwork that inspired Blade Runner. Covers by Moritat and Scott Keating.

volume.name: Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?

description: George and Sophia are safe, but Paul can't leave the monstrous Medusa loose on this unsuspecting world. He must go back and defeat one of the most dangerous creatures of myth and legend! Is she too strong for him now that he is no longer immortal? Can he resist the temptation she brings him from the gods?

Revenge will be hers! The stunning conclusion to this twisted post-Hurricane Katrina story that can't be missed! Nola continues her bloody rampage through New Orleans as she puts a bullet in every problem she has in the city. From Chris Gorak (Right at Your Door) and scripted by Heroes graphic novel writer Pierluigi Cothran!

So, how exactly does a struggling model become a professional killer? And what happens when said model-turned-killer ends up getting trashed and shooting the wrong guy - the really wrong guy? The party's just getting started at FORGETLESS club night, but for our girl Sara, it might already be over.
name: Rememberful?_03

description: Covering from the last issue from the second volume, this issues warps things up when she faces Flaw and The Child.
name: Kismet

description: The exclusive four-issue prequel to the upcoming blockbuster horror film THE CRAZIES from Overture Films begins here. Meet Rory Hamill, aka 'Patient Zero', the first victim of a pathogenic rage that will change the world as we know it. Something is wrong with the water supply in Hopman Bog and the ramifications are lethal for all involved. Can a simple farmer stand in the way of a biological terror the likes of which have never been seen before? The results will not be for the squeamish.
name: Hopman Bog

description: The raging pathogen continues its vicious course of destruction as its origin is slowly unveiled. Bill Farnum, a mild mannered husband and father battles a slow descent into rabid craziness. What chance does an average family man stand when the monster inside is unleashed? It's domestic horror at its finest as the exclusive prequel to the hit Overture Films release THE CRAZIES continues its deadly path of small town destruction.
name: Dwyer Creek

description: Water and terror flow downstream to the banks of Black Pond and the spookiness of the town morgue. Charlie Finley, propietor of said establishment, is a good and decent man - until confronted with the limitless rage of a biological pathogen. It's one man's descent into terrible, horrible madness as the exclusive prequel to the Overture Films release THE CRAZIES continues. There is no everlasting peace to be found here - only bloodthirsty craziness. Also, bear witness as the true origin of the vicious pathogen continues to be revealed.
name: Black Pond

description: It all comes down to this, the fourth and final issue in this exclusive prequel to the Overture Films release THE CRAZIES. Terror and destruction has finally come downstream to the small town of Ogden Marsh and panic is spreading faster than the pathogen itself. The government has arrived with nefarious plans as survivors attempt to make their escape amidst a band of bloodthirsty crazies. The true, evil nature of the pathogen is finally revealed and the world around us will never be the same again. There will be blood - oh yes - there will be LOTS of blood. Can anyone possibly survive to tell the tale?
name: Ogden Marsh

description:
Two mystery cases collide, as Batman gets closer to finding a missing socialite while Batwoman uncovers a gruesome new villain who has grafted knives onto his skin. There will be blood ‚Äì and souvenirs of victims' flesh ‚Äì in "Cutter" part 2!

And in The Question's co-feature, the unknown mastermind behind the gun-running scheme hires a professional killer to take care of some unwanted female companionship. When Zeiss sets his sights on Huntress and The Question, bullets will fly and blood will run!
name: Cutter, Part 2 of 3; Pipeline, Chapter Two Part Three

description: For Thomas Andrew Tresser, aka Nemesis, the world of metahuman espionage is never what it seems. After his recent "reeducation" at the hands of the Global Peace Agency, Nemesis finds himself thrust back into the real world with enemies seemingly around every corner. Tasked with uncovering the truth about his mission and the true identities of those hoping to unleash a great evil on the world, Nemesis is forced to confront the fact that he may not be able to trust anybody in the universe ‚Äì including himself.
name: Part 1: Close Your Eyes

description:
ADVENTURE COMICS ships twice this month as this spring's Superman event "Brainiac and The Legion of Super-Heroes" starts with a prologue in #8 and reaches a boiling point in #9!

Starting way back in "The Lightning Saga," various clues have been planted about a group of Legionnaires undercover in the 21st century. Who are they and why are they here? And what does their mission have to do with the fate of New Krypton? James Robinson (SUPERMAN) and Juli√°n L√≥pez (WORLD'S FINEST) may have an answer or two!

Meanwhile, in a tale of the 31st century by Sterling Gates (SUPERGIRL) and Clayton Henry (ADVENTURE COMICS), the Legion of Super-Heroes infiltrates a hidden Legion of Super-Villains base! The horrifying plans Brainiac 5 discovers inside will alter Superman's life ‚Äì FOREVER!

Plus, in the co-feature by Eric Trautmann (ACTION COMICS) and newcomer Pier Gallo, learn more about General Lane's Human Defense Corps ‚Äì Earth's best line of defense against the looming Kryptonian threat!
name: Last Stand of New Krypton Prologue, Part One: The Future Is Prologue; Last Stand of New Krypton Prologue, Part Two: The Future is Now; Awake, Part 1

description:
"HARD AS ROCK"

Off the coast of the Galapagos Islands, something hideous, something so deliciously amoral has vanquished the tranquility and shattered the peace - DEADPOOL! The legend no one can forget has been missing for years...yes, we're talking about It! The Living Colossus, the 30-foot-tall stone statue brought to life by wheelchair-bound Robert "Bob" O'Bryan. Enlisted by O'Bryan's niece, Deadpool takes a dive, plunging down to the ocean floor in search of the stone statue. But something more heinous than Deadpool's thoughts when he's watching lingerie football lurks in the ocean depths. And underwater, nobody can hear your hilarious one-liners!
name: Hard As Rock

description: She's left her apocalyptic world for this one. Her mother was a heroine, her father a rampaging HULK. What path is the Savage She-Hulk called Lyra on, and why has it led her to add her might to the Wizard's Frightful Four? See how some of the toughest women in the Marvel Universe tip the balance of power in the Fall of the Hulks with this exciting miniseries by Jeff Parker (AGENTS OF ATLAS, FALL OF THE HULKS ALPHA) and Salva Espin (INCREDIBLE HERCULES)!
name: The Savage Sex

volume.name: Fall of the Hulks: The Savage She-Hulks

description: This is the big one! After the catastrophes seen in issues #5 and #6, a hero loses control, leading to an unexpected ending that will fundamentally change the lives of the World's Greatest Heroes forever. This issue launches a major storyline in the DC Universe and is not to be missed!
name: Justice

description: Mister No takes a businessman, Walter Murphy, Murphy‚Äôs wife and the beautiful Brenda Morris to Trinidad. On the island, however, a terrible Indio sect of "Thugs" is operating, and more than once they make an attempt on Mister No‚Äôs life. Hailed by the strong Hindu minority, the thugs want to build an Indian nation in the heart of America and it seems that the merciless Surat Khan is their leader!
name: Gli Spietati

description: The Thugs kidnap Brenda Morris, to persuade the businessman Walter Murphy not to buy a piece of land. To save her, Mister No enters the palace of Surat Khan. However, the influential character makes a shocking revelation to our Jerry‚Ä¶
name: Surat Khan

description: Brenda has been captured by Prince Ahmed, who intends to seize the land that the businessman Murphy was buying, and which is rich in oil fields. Still looking for the girl, Mister No goes to an opium den, where he meets a strange ally‚Ä¶
name: La Casa dei Sogni Colorati

description: A meteorite crashes in the Amazon forest and, in the same zone, a scientific expedition led by Professor Parker disappears. Some months later, Mister No is hired by a girl who says she is Linda, Parker‚Äôs daughter. But the would-be Linda steals Jerry‚Äôs Piper: who is she really?
name: La Spedizione Scomparsa

description: Mister No and Esse-Esse fight against the criminal Blenda, who, with her accomplice Sinclair, has kidnapped the men on Parker‚Äôs expedition. But our heroes also have to fight against weird plants and insects in the forest, which have become monstrous as a result of the radiation from the meteorite!
name: La Foresta dei Mutanti

description: Mister No meets an old friend, Larry Tree. In a bar in Manaus, chatting to the beautiful Flor and a young Argentinean, he tells how he became the first hero of the legendary Flying Tigers. It all began in September of 1940, when, in Caniff Field, he met Bat Barlington‚Ä¶
name: Vento di Guerra

description: Mister No continues to tell about when he was contacted by Bill Carson, who was part of the American Volunteer Group of the Colonel Chennault, a group of mercenaries (in reality, authorized by the American government) that fought for General Chang Kai-Shek in China. Jerry and Bat accepted Carson‚Äôs suggestion and joined the future Flying Tigers‚Ä¶
name: Le Tigri Volanti

description: Mister No‚Äôs story of the past in the Flying Tigers reaches its climax. Colonel Chennault needed six men for a special mission in China. Mister No and Bat Barlington were among these six. In China, Jerry took part in his first air battles and saw the real nature of war‚Ä¶
name: Cielo Giallo

description: In front of a attentive public, in a Manaus bar, Mister No is about to finish his story of his past adventures. Wounded in an air battle, he was given first aid and then found himself in a village where the mysterious Colonel Kung held sway. He flirted with the beautiful Li Chao. But Kung turned out to be an enemy, Li Chao was hiding a secret and, for the first time, Jerry would be called Mister No!
name: Il Mio Nome √® Mister No

description: Mister No takes his last client, Merril, to the border between Mexico and Guatemala, where there is a rubber plantation owned by the Kentucky Gum Company. For months, the Chicleros, the gum cultivators, have not been paid, and as Merril has been unable to get money from the company, the Chicleros revolt, leaving a trail of death among their bosses!
name: La Notte dei Machetes

description: Escaping by the skin of their teeth from the rage of the Chicleros, Mister No and Harry Kramer of the Kentucky Gum Company seek refuge among the ruins of an ancient Mayan temple to take shelter from a violent downpour. But during the night, they receive an unexpected visit‚Ä¶
name: Agguato nella Citt√† Sepolta

description: Among the Maya ruins, there is an assassin wandering around who wants to set free the Lacandones Indios, who are being exploited by the white men. He is killing all of Mister No‚Äôs companions, maintaining he is the reincarnation of the great Mayan of Bonampak!
name: Il Giustiziere di Bonampak
